               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281023-237-person1254">
                  LEVY 
                  JACOBS
               <interp inst="t18281023-237-person1254" type="surname" value="JACOBS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281023-237-person1254" type="given" value="LEVY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281023-237-person1254" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 14th of October the prisoner brought two fur tippets to my shop for sale; I asked how he came by them - he said he had them to sell, and that he, manufactured them; I asked where he lived - he said in White Horse-court, Cow-cross; I took the tippets, and went to the place - he kept dodging me about for some time; at last we went to the house, and saw two or three women; I asked if he lived there - they said Yes; I asked his trade - they said he was a working smith, and they did not know of his having the tippets; they were astonished on seeing them - he was going to snatch at them, and he did get them from me; people came round, and said I wanted to make a property of him - he then went away into Cow-cross; a friend of mine came up - we went after him, and found him in Cow-cross with the tippets; I took them from him - he followed me through Sharp's-alley to West-street, and there made a stop; a mob gathered - an officer came up, and took him.</p>
               <p>JACOB HARRIS I <rs id="t18281023-237-viclabel1379" type="occupation">keep a furrier's shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281023-237-victim1253 t18281023-237-viclabel1379"></join> in <placeName id="t18281023-237-crimeloc1380">Peter-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18281023-237-crimeloc1380" type="placeName" value="Peter-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18281023-237-crimeloc1380" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281023-237-off1377 t18281023-237-crimeloc1380"></join>. The officer gave me these tippets at Hatton-gardon - they are mine, and were safe about a quarter-past one o'clock on the 14th of October; I was out of the shop about ten minutes, and then missed them.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I bought them of a decent young woman in the street, and wanted to sell them to pay my rent; I asked 1l. for them - Jacobs offered 9s., and said if I would not take that he would take me into custody.</p>
               <p>LEVY JACOBS. He asked no price - he was beastly drunk.</p>
